comment: thanks for being at the stream to talk to

Cheesecake sounds nice. I think I'm gonna make some Tiramisu this weekend.
It has cheese in it, so technically it's a cheesecake, too... right?
I think I'ma go out and get some convenience store food.  Maybe some cheesecake since they have it and chat has gone that direction
It's so refreshing to just play a game and enjoy just about every moment
Might get into it again another time in the future to platinum it, but for now, I really just feel content in beating it.
That game is definitely on my list of "to plays"
That said, also resubbed to WoW, soooooo might be a bit, haha
And I take it it's like a Bethesda game, but actually good? :P
If Bethesda made an RPG in their stat based era of Morrowind, made an a Fallout universe, with the graphics of today, and using writers that actualy knew how to write stories...
And also with programmers who know how to eliminate basic bugs? :ptv-snicker:
Their was one major bug in my playthrough that made an NPC and their quest unavailable
Also, picking up stuff from boxes and corpses was constantly bugged where you'd have to look at, then look away from, then look back to the object in order to see what you could take.
Literally constantly, affected maybe every third lootable object.
Only took a second or two to remedy, but add those seconds up over hundreds and hundreds of lootings....
I might need to start wearing headphones while gaming
Bethesda will die.  I'm calling it now.  The next game they launch is going to be a flop because they've garnered so much bad rep over the past year.
